## Architecture (Deep Mode)

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["fetch_financials"] --> B["analyze_financials"]
    B --> C["retrieve_risks<br/>(hybrid: dense + sparse)"]
    C --> D["summarize_risks"]
    D -->|deep| E["peer_comparison"]
    D -->|quick| J["assemble_report"]
    E --> F["quant_analysis<br/>(DCF + WACC)"]
    F --> G["thesis"]
    G --> H["reflection<br/>(Senior Analyst)"]
    H -->|rejected & rev < 2| G
    H -->|approved| I["confidence_scoring"]
    I --> J
    J --> K["END"]
```

## Key Design Decisions

- **GLM-4.7 via OpenAI SDK**: Uses `openai` Python package with `base_url` pointed to Zhipu's OpenAI-compatible endpoint — no separate SDK needed
- **Sparse vectors**: BM25-lite with hash-based term indexing (no external tokenizer dependency)
- **Reflection loop**: Max 2 cycles to prevent infinite loops; graceful fallback on errors
- **DCF is deterministic**: LLM only estimates input parameters; all math runs in pure Python

